{"id": "EUVD-2023-0871", "enisaUuid": "10c486b4-5d89-3d0e-a3fe-ded37707ffe3", "description": "Vega is a visualization grammar, a declarative format for creating, saving, and sharing interactive visualization designs. The Vega `scale` expression function has the ability to call arbitrary functions with a single controlled argument. The scale expression function passes a user supplied argument group to getScale, which is then used as if it were an internal context. The context.scales[name].value is accessed from group and called as a function back in scale. This can be exploited to escape the Vega expression sandbox in order to execute arbitrary JavaScript. This issue has been fixed in version 5.13.1.", "datePublished": "2023-03-03T23:48:41", "dateUpdated": "2025-02-25T15:01:48", "baseScore": 6.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/vega/vega/security/advisories/GHSA-4vq7-882g-wcg4", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-26486", "https://github.com/vega/vega", "https://github.com/vega/vega/releases/tag/v5.23.0", "https://github.dev/vega/vega/blob/72b9b3bbf912212e7879b6acaccc84aff969ef1c/packages/vega-functions/src/functions/scale.js#L36-L37", "https://github.dev/vega/vega/blob/72b9b3bbf912212e7879b6acaccc84aff969ef1c/packages/vega-functions/src/scales.js#L6", "https://vega.github.io/editor/#-hIIECQYEAL5wmHXeEIkAw1yomFAA"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-26486", "GHSA-4vq7-882g-wcg4"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.19, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00ff7f0a-77b5-3619-85e3-8536fd278b04", "product": {"name": "vega"}, "product_version": "< 5.13.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "4fd8a1c9-bf0c-370f-86fc-63e03ae10abf", "vendor": {"name": "vega"}}], "isExploited": false}